node.text:
If you’ve been out to our distillery, there’s a good chance you’ve run into Rabbi Gil at some point. Whether he’s guiding folks on the tour or handing out quality control shots, any time spent with Gil is guaranteed to be a good time.
-
As many of you know, Gil is one helluva storyteller. And in this video, he’s taken on the task of telling the tale of how Garrison Brothers came to be. So sit back, relax, and pour yourself a glass of the finest as you listen to the legend of Garrison Brothers from Rabbi Gil.
-
#salud #garrisonbrothers #drinktexasbourbon

node.text:
GLASS: Rocks
GARNISH: Orange Peel and Maraska Maraschino Cherries

INGREDIENTS
2 oz. Garrison Brothers Small Batch
.5 oz. Simple Syrup
2 Dashes Fee Brothers Chocolate Bitters

METHOD
In a mixing glass combine simple syrup, bitters, and Garrison Brothers Small Batch. Add ice and stir until chilled (15 seconds). Strain into a rocks glass over a large rock and garnish with an expressed orange peel and Maraska Maraschino Cherries.

node.title: The GB Chocolate Old Fashioned with Fee Brothers Bitters

-

-

For years, he was adamantly opposed to adding anything extra to the already-perfect bourbon pour. His preferred cocktail of choice? “Mix 2 parts Garrison Brothers with 1 part glass.”
-
That is, however, until the birth of the Garrison Brothers Bourbon Brawl.
-
Day 5 of our 8-day celebration of National Bourbon Week goes out to all the incredible bartenders and mixologists out there. After watching these artists put their creative spins on Garrison Brothers Bourbon by adding unexpected ingredients and techniques––and then tasting these delicious concoctions––his mind was forever changed.
-
Adding one’s favorite touches to their bourbon of choice makes the whole experience even more personal and often enhances the delicious flavors of our Texas Bourbon. We encourage y’all to come up with your own signature drinks and share them with loved ones.
-
Happy Bartending, y’all.
-
#salud #garrisonbros #bourboncocktail #mixology #drinktexasbourbon

Balmorhea is far more than the hard-to-pronounce name of our award-winning, twice-barreled Bourbon Whiskey. It’s the name of an 80-year-old Texas State Park and swimming hole, which happens to be one of the largest spring-fed pools in the world. In fact, the dazzling blue water inspired the wax color that each and every bottle is dipped in.
-
To date, we’ve been able to raise around $35,000 from bottle sales alone for the preservation and beautification of the park with the help of the amazing folks at @texasparkswildlife -
Here’s to protecting our beautiful state’s wildlife and natural habitats.
-

Back and more bourbon-y than ever!⁠⁠
-⁠⁠
Here’s to the 2021 Garrison Brothers Bourbon Takeover of America presented by TimeOut. That’s right – our annual celebration of all things bourbon has expanded outside of the great state of Texas and will take place in several states across the country.⁠⁠
-⁠⁠
Like in years past, we’re partnering with chefs, bartenders and mixologists across the country to bring you this year’s Bourbon Takeover, presented by our awesome friends at TimeOut.⁠⁠
 -⁠⁠
From September 13th to September 24th, 2021, these tastemakers will showcase their love for Garrison Brothers Bourbon by incorporating our Small Batch or HoneyDew Bourbon into a unique, limited-time dish and/or cocktail special. Featuring meals and cocktails from some of the best bars and restaurants across America, this will be an incredible experience for both cocktail aficionados and bourbon newcomers alike.⁠⁠
 -⁠⁠
Stay tuned for more info on this year's Bourbon Takeover, visit the link in our bio to learn more, and tag a friend or 2 in the comments below that you’ll hitting up your favorite participating restaurants and bars with!⁠⁠

-⁠⁠
Josh’s cocktail, the “Texas Rose”, wowed our judges with its vibrant appearance and magnificent flavor, and is available for purchase in our one-of-a-kind cocktail kit (check the link in our bio for more info). Christian Orlando of The Stand NYC called it “nothing short of perfect” – but we believe Dan Garrison summed it up best: “I like this so damn much.”⁠⁠
-⁠⁠
Thank you to all of our competitors who brought their A-game to the Finals! And for those of y’all looking to try the Texas Rose yourself, it’s not too late to order your 2021 Bourbon Brawl Champion Cocktail Kit. Use the link in our bio to snag yours right now, which will include all of the ingredients necessary to whip up this $10,000 winning cocktail. ⁠⁠

To learn more about Josh and the Texas Rose, head on over to the Bourbon Blog on our website to check out the full story!⁠⁠

When Dan Garrison opened the gates this morning, he was greeted with a line that stretched back from the distillery all the way to 290. After a healthy amount of breakfast tacos and breakfast bourbon, we were amazed to see our entire Guadalupe stock of just under 1,000 bottles sell out in under 2 hours. 
-
Thanks to all of y’all who made the trip out and got a bottle of our newest Nectar Of The Gods! Although we’re all sold out at the ranch, you’ll start seeing bottles pop up on liquor store shelves within’ the next few weeks. Happy hunting, y’all!

node.text:
It's days like today that serve as the perfect reminder why we make the best damn bourbon in the world: because we've got the best damn people in the world drinking it.
-
We'd barely begun to open the gates for the day when Renee and Shawn over at @bourbon_cigar_mischief pulled up in their RV, claiming their spot as the first in line for the release of our new Port-finished Guadalupe bourbon tomorrow at 8 a.m. When asked why they showed up a whopping 22 hours early, their answer was very simple: "We had to be first in line for Guadalupe. I can't wait to taste the port, it sounds fabulous, absolutely divine."
-
And if that wasn't enough, no more than ten minutes later we were joined by @rdoza13. As he put it, "I would've been first if I hadn't stopped to get the crew donuts." And as we all know, good donuts, much like good bourbon, are always appreciated!
-
Thank you to Renee, Shawn, Ramon, and all the rest of you crazy beautiful people who help make each release even bigger and better than the one before. When you get a bunch of good folks together to make some good memories and sip the newest Nectar Of The Gods, you know it's going to be a good time.
-
See y'all bright and early tomorrow morning, when we'll be introducing the world to our most refined bourbon yet. Salud.
-
#salud #DrinkTexasBourbon #guadalupe

Just visit texasmonthly.com/bourbonbrawl at 7:30PM CST on July 29th to see 8 of the top bartenders and mixologists in the country go head-to-head, crafting the most epic bourbon cocktails imaginable, for a shot at $10,000 and an entire barrel of Garrison Brothers bourbon.⁠⁠

Additionally, there’s still time to order your official Bourbon Brawl cocktail kit – a special package containing all of the ingredients needed to craft the winning cocktail. Kits will come in two sizes with everything you need to make the winning cocktail. The large will feature a 750ml bottle of the award-winning Small Batch bourbon whiskey that is meant to be shared with friends, but if you are looking for a more intimate cocktail experience, the small kit will feature a 375ml Boot Flask bottle. Kits will be shipped out beginning on August 9th. To grab your kit, use the link in our bio or visit: cocktailcourier.com/cocktail/bourbon-brawl-kit/⁠⁠

node.text:
“The mouthfeel alone is worth the ticket price. It’s simply amazing.”⁠⁠
-⁠⁠
Just one more week until our Port-Finished Guadalupe Bourbon makes its official splash and Master Distiller Donnis Todd might be the most excited of us all, proposing that this exquisite bourbon is head and shoulders above all the other bourbons he’s created because of the incredible mouthfeel and finish.⁠⁠
-⁠⁠
Awhile back, Donnis stumbled across several 4-year-old barrels that had beautiful notes of chocolate, cinnamon, honey, and raspberry… the same characteristics that one might find in a great port wine. To highlight these beautiful flavors, he tracked down some wet, tawny port barrels from the northern part of Portugal and filled them with the Texas straight bourbon whiskey.⁠⁠
-⁠⁠
After resting for an additional 2 years inside the port barrels, the result is the most refined Garrison Brothers bourbon to date. And according to Donnis: “It’s so good, I think folks will drink it at happy hour, they’ll drink it with a meal, and they might pass on the cheesecake and get one more pour of Guadalupe to wrap up the night.”⁠⁠
-⁠⁠
See y’all next Saturday at 8 a.m.!⁠⁠
